Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper is about speech recognition, which falls under natural language processing (NLP) and speech processing. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is also a likely category as the paper deals with speech signals and their processing. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper proposes a new architecture for deep learning networks. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper deals with machine learning and speech recognition, which are both subfields of AI. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses real-time applications and latency control.
